org.datalorax.populace.core.populate.instance

Class DefaultTypeInstanceFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.datalorax.populace.core.populate.instance.DefaultTypeInstanceFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InstanceFactory

    public class DefaultTypeInstanceFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements InstanceFactory
    Instance factory for handling non-concrete types e.g. interface and abstract types. The factory delegates any concrete types its called with to the concreteFactory provided to the constructor. For non-concrete types the factory creates an instance of the defaultType passed to the constructor, using the concreteFactory passed in.

        public DefaultTypeInstanceFactory(java.lang.Class<T> baseType,
                                  java.lang.Class<? extends T> defaultType,
                                  InstanceFactory concreteFactory)
        Type Parameters:
        T - The base type this factory will be used to instantiate.
        Parameters:
        baseType - the base type that this instance factory supports, i.e. the lowest common denominator.
        defaultType - the type to instantiate when a call to InstanceFactory.createInstance(Class, Object, InstanceFactories) is for a non-concrete type. The type must be a concrete sub-type of baseType
        concreteFactory - the instance factory to delegate to for concrete types and to create instances of

    • Method Detail

      • createInstance

        public <T> T createInstance(java.lang.Class<? extends T> type,
                            java.lang.Object parent,
                            InstanceFactories instanceFactories)
        Description copied from interface: InstanceFactory
        Create a new instance of rawType. If the factory does not support the type it will return null. If an error occurred while attempting to create an instance it will throw a PopulatorException. Otherwise the call will return a new instance.
        Specified by:
        createInstance in interface InstanceFactory
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type to create
        Parameters:
        type - the type to create
        parent - the parent instance, which is needed to create inner class instances. Can be null.
        instanceFactories - the set of instance factories defined in the system
        Returns:
        a new instance or null if the type is not supported by the factory.
